		<h3>Daily Fiction</h3>
		<h1>Dreamt I Found You</h1>
		<h2>By Jimin Han</h2>
		<div class="img-excerpt-container">
			<div class="img-container"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/dreamt-i-found-you.jpg" alt="Dreamt I Found You"></div>
			<div class="excerpt-container"><div class="excerpt"><em>The following is from Jimin Han's </em>Dreamt I Found You<em>. Han was born in Seoul, South Korea, and grew up in Providence, Rhode Island; Dayton, Ohio; and Jamestown, New York. She is the author of </em>A Small Revolution <em>and </em>The Apology<em>. She has written for NPR’s Weekend America, Poets and Writers Magazine, Catapult Magazine, Platypus Press, and Citric Acid Literary Journal, among others. She teaches at Sarah Lawrence College and Pace University, as well as at community writing centers. She lives outside New York City.</em></div></div>
